But, he warned, the hurricane center still is following three other weather systems that have moved into the Atlantic between the United States and Africa, and another storm in the Pacific. Before the hurricane warning system was established, a storm of Hugo's power would have cost thousands of lives. In the Caribbean, we were not so certain the word got out. In the center was Sheets himself. On the other side were the media _ a pack of reporters, camera operators and technicians, jockeying for seconds of Sheets' time and tidbits of his expertise. 